description:
Audra McDonald, Phylicia Rashad, Denée Benton, Jordan Donica, and more discuss the show’s exploration of 1880s colorism and its lasting impact today. With the introduction of the Kirklands, the show contrasts the Scotts, offering a more nuanced portrayal of the Black experience during the Gilded Age.
